<seg id=2> In the first round of talks, the different sides have come to some common points.  The meeting laid down the necessary foundation for future talks and also further clarified the objective, route and guiding principle to resolve the nuclear problem in Korean Peninsula. </seg>
<seg id=3> In the past several months, the relevant sides have all insisted to resolve the nuclear problem in Korean Peninsula peacefully through dialogue.  Based on the foundation of the results of first round of talks, different sides have proceeded with a wide range of coordination and discussions at different levels such as to contribute untiring efforts to hold the second round meeting at an earlier date. </seg>
