<seg id=3> This is a clear signal that high tech industry in the area is heading for a rebound. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> In its annual report, the "2004 Index of Silicon Valley", the non-profit institution "Joint Venture: Silicon Valley Network" said the jobless rate in Silicon Valley has decreased from 10% in the second quarter of 2002 to 5% in the second quarter of 2003. </seg>
<seg id=5> The report believed that jobless rate would continue to drop as the high tech industry gradually recovers. </seg>
