<p>
<seg id=2> (AFP report from Davos, Switzerland, January 19) A research report issued today by the World Economic Forum (WEF) and US consultant Watson Wyatt Worldwide pointed out that European Union's output volume would fall down by 50% in the global economic output volume in 2050 due to the shrinkage of the labor population. </seg>
<seg id=3> In contrast, the sufficient labor supply in developing countries such as India and China will help promote the economic development. </seg>
