<DOC docid="PD20040202.001" sysid="che">
<p>
<seg id=1> After the world entered the new century, African countries were confronted by an important and serious challenge because of economic globalization. </seg>
<seg id=2> Leaders of African countries have come to realize more and more clearly that Africa cannot afford to let slip the excellent opportunity and should start immediately to find policies and measures to deal with it. </seg>
<seg id=3> On July 9th, 2002 the African Union was formally set up and began to work. From then on African countries, on the one hand, began to actively implement "the New Partnership for Africa's Development", worked hard to develop economy and strive to get rid of the unfavorable plight in economic globalization as soon as possible. On the other hand they made special efforts to settle the issues of armed conflicts - a main obstacle to the renaissance cause of Africa so as to create a united, peaceful and stable environment. </seg>
<seg id=4> The general situation in Africa at present is relaxing and the hot spot issues are cooling down. The countries are more and more eager to put an end to the armed conflicts. </seg>
<seg id=5> Backed up by UN and the international community, the influential regional organization in Africa, the regional powers and famous statesmen have taken positive actions and stepped up their efforts in settling regional conflicts and removing internal turmoil. Some conflicts and turmoil which lasted for years have been basically brought under control. </seg>
<seg id=6> For instance a national unity government was set up in Congo (Kinshasa) in June last year; in July Sao Tome and Principe solved the coup d'etat crisis with peaceful means; in August the Libyan government signed a peace accord with the anti-government armed forces in the Ghana capital of Accra; in September the Sudanese government began a key talk with the anti-government forces in the south, which broke the deadlock of the peace process; in October the various armed and political factions in Somalia began their peace talk in Kenya and talked about the nationwide peace process; in November the Burundi government signed a peace accord with the anti-government troops; etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Of course the stability in Africa at present is still fragile and the fruits of peace need to be consolidated. Some potential and existing armed conflicts are to be finally settled. </seg>
<seg id=8> At the same time there is still a great gap between African countries and developing countries in Asia and other continents in terms of the speed of economic development. These are the unfavorable elements for African development. </seg>
<seg id=9> How to deal with the challenges of economic globalization effectively in African countries and realize the African dream of renaissance, the African people have to make long-term and arduous endeavor. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
