<DOC docid="AFC20040106.0019" sysid="che">
<hl>
<seg id=1> The USA Has Started to Take Photos And Fingerprints of Foreign Travelers Who Enter The Country </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (AFP in Washington on 5th) At a time when Singapore where the largest airport in Asia is located is for the airliners to be equipped with armed police to cope with terrorist threat, the USA has started today the new measure of taking photos and fingerprints of foreign travelers entering America. </seg>
<seg id=3> The Washington authority tightens its screening of foreign travelers when worries over aviation security are rising all over the world. Over the past week the afore-mentioned worries have caused several flights into and out of America to be cancelled fo the time being. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The new measure of taking photos and fingerprints is only for those travelers who cannot enter USA without visas. Generally the number of such travelers is predicted to be 23 million this whole year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The Homeland Security Department which is responsible for the implementation of the United States visitor and Immigrant Status Indicator Technology (US-VISIT) points out that 28 countries, mostly European nations, are exempt from the above procedures. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Immigration organization attack this plan as an infringement on citizens' right of liberty and as a step towards a monitored society. The Secretary of Homeland Security Ridge argues hard in favor of the plan. </seg>
<seg id=7> When interviewed by NBC, Ridge said "one of the priority responsibilities of any government is to ensure the border safety. We work out this plan just to fulfil this duty. I don't think it is rash. Obviously nobody cares much about this practice which in fact takes no more than 15 seconds." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> By 2005 all the entrances by land, by sea or by air will be equipped with the photo- and fingerprint-taking devices. </seg>
<seg id=9> All the American visas and passports will finally include photos and fingerprints "distinguishing marks biological identity ". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Before the above plan was implemented, the USA began to raise its alarm grade for terrorist attacks in December last year. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
