<seg id=8> He also said that the summit has "added new vigor to the regional cooperation." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> The state heads and foreign ministers of Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka signed at the summit the South Asia Free Tread Agreement "SAFTA", the Social Charter, the Anti-Poverty Plan, the Anti-Terrorism agreement and "Islamabad Declaration." </seg>
