<seg id=1> Syria Criticizes Israel for Lack of Sincerity in Its Invitation of Syrian President to Visit Israel </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (AFP in Damascus on 12th) Israeli President Katsav today invites Syrian President Al-Assad to visit Jerusalem for peace talks. The Syrian officials denounces the invitation as lack of sincerity and accuses Israel of trying to avoid the Middle East peace process of land for peace. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Katsav said on Israeli Public Radio Station early today: "I invite President Al-Assad to visit Jerusalem so that conditions of a peace accord can be talked seriously with Israeli's leader." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Katsav also said: "Al-Assad will be welcomed and he should not set prerequisites." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The Syrian Minister of Overseas Syrian Nationals Al-Sharaa indicates when interviewed by the American Cable News Network (CNN) that Israel must explicitly express its willingness to resume the talk from where the negotiation broke off 4 years ago. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Al-Sharaa points out that the invitation sent by Katsav is not "a sincere response" to President Al-Assad who appealed last month to Israel to resume contact. He accuses Katsav of trying to get the lime-light. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The Syrian official news agency SANA quotes a nameless senior official who accuses Israel of trying to avoid the Middle East peace process based on land for peace. </seg>
<seg id=8> This official said that "it is not a question of visiting or taking the initiative; the purpose of recent Israeli speeches is to avoid peace process." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> This official also states: "Any plan or measure for partial settlement cannot bring peace to the Middle East." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> When talking with Al-Assad's late father King Al-Assad Senior, the then Israeli premier Barak agreed to withdraw from almost all Golan Heights and to keep only the east coast of Sea of Galiaee as a narrow corridor. </seg>
<seg id=11> However, the Damascus authorities refuses to accept the proposal and wishes Israel to return all the land on Golan Heights which was occupied by Israel in 1976 War and annexed in 1981. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
<DOC docid="AFC20040113.0026" sysid="che">
<hl>
<seg id=1> Rifts within The Commanding System of The Largest Rebellious Group in Liberia Are Deepened </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (AFP in Monrovia on 12th) After the Leader of "LURD" Conneh was expelled, power struggle within this largest rebellious army group is growing tense. A leader of the rebellious army insists that Conneh still maintain the power. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> LURD rose up in 1999 to fight against the former president Taylor and kindled the 4-year-long civil war in Liberia. Now it occupies about 4 fifths of Liberia. </seg>
<seg id=4> In mid-August last year Taylor agreed to exile to Nigeria so as to pave way for peace agreement in this western African country. The former government, the rebellious army and the out-parties formed an interim government. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> But a group which calls itself "High Military Command" of LURD accuses Conneh of selling the post of LURD in the transitional government to fill his own pocket. Some time ago it adopted Aisha Keita Conneh,  the divorced wife of Conneh, as the new leader. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> But Dweh, parliament speaker of the transitional government and founder of LURD, insists that only the national executive committee of LURD has the right to recall the leader of the organization. </seg>
<seg id=7> He told the media the night before last: "I founded LURD in Nigeria; I can guarantee to the Liberian people that there is no rift within LURD and nothing can sabotage the peace process." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Dweh attributes the internal strife to the behind-the-scene manipulation of the transitional government leader Bryant and other LURD leaders who serve in the transitional government. </seg>
<seg id=9> Bryant who used to be a merchant was appointed last October as the leader of this war-ridden country until 2005 general election. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Dweh accuses the ministers of justice, communications and labor of colluding with Aisha Conneh,supported by Bryant,promising her that she would be the LUDR leader as soon as Conneh is out of power. </seg>
<seg id=11> He warns that, if Bryant continues to violate the peace accord, the warring parties will return to Accra where the accord was prepared and discuss whether Bryant should be replaced. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
<DOC docid="AFC20040113.0056" sysid="che">
<hl>
<seg id=1> Former US Boxer Charges A Boxing Advertising Company with Bribing Him to Purposely Loose in The Match </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (AFP in New York on 12th) According to New York Daily News, the former US boxer Rose says that Top Rank Company, US Professional Boxing Promoter, provides 5,000 USD as bribery to make him deliberately loose in the game. </seg>
<seg id=3> Top Rank Company run by Arum is now being investigated by the US Federal Bureau of Investigation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The 34-year-old Rose says that, several weeks before his match with another American boxer Esch nicknamed Butterbean in December 1995, two representatives of Top Rank Company called at his house. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Rose told the newspaper: "Soon after mid-day when I was having a rest at home, somebody knocked on the door. Through the peeping hole I saw two white employees of Top Rank. They wanted to talk about my boxing match with Butterbean." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> "They said: We have brought some money for you, a large sum. They wanted me to lose and not to defeat Butterbean." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Rose told the 1995 incident to the investigators; the case is part of the 20-month-long investigation into embezzlements in the boxing fields. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Rose turned down the bribery and knocked down the ever-victorious Esch in the second round of the match on Madison Square Garden. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> New York Daily News went to the residence of Esch in Alabama and asked whether or not he believed what Rose said. Esch defended Top Rank,saying: "Rose is no match in strength. How is it possible for you to ask a boxer to purposely lose when his record is 1 win and 6 defeats? I don't think Top Rank violates the law." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> FBI went to Las Vegas on 6th to inspect the headquarters of Top Rank and confiscated some of its financial and medical documents and computers. </seg>
<seg id=11> It is reported that FBI is collecting evidences about pre-game decision of results including the September championship match between Mosley and Hoya. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
