</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> They claim that the report had been prepared before US helicopters were attacked on 3 occasions this month. However, the recent 3 attacks further confirm the conclusion of the report. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The report aims to provide US pilots with methods of how to evade attacks by such weapons. The officials are reluctant to discuss the new contents recently discovered. </seg>
<seg id=6> But judging from the new round of attacks in Iraq, people cannot help feeling worried that Iraqi guerrillas have carefully studied the fighting style of American aircrafts. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Researchers have found that Iraqi guerrillas have used SA-16 shoulder-fired missiles more than once, which is really worrying. </seg>
<seg id=8> Missiles with such precision guidance systems can hardly be evaded by pilots. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> A senior US pilot in the Persian Gulf said: "Every successful attack of our aircrafts is a great victory strategically for our enemy. </seg>
<seg id=10> Not only it is covered by media but also it is a clear-cut judgement of victory or defeat. Therefore, our enemy believes it is a useful maneuver." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> Since October 25 last year, 9 US helicopters have already been downed or crashed with at least 49 US soldiers killed. </seg>
