</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The Indonesian officials pointed out earlier that the bird flu in November last year which victimized poultry on Java and Bali Islands was Newcastle disease. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Ministry of Agriculture spokesman Priyono said this morning that there is no sign of bird flu epidemic in Indonesia so far. </seg>
<seg id=7> He told AFP in the evening that it was not certain whether the epidemic was caused by H5N1 virus. </seg>
<seg id=8> Most of the deaths from bird flu in Vietnam were infected by H5N1 virus. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> The spokesman said that the Newcastle Disease and A-type bird flu have resulted in the death of 4.7 million poultry since November last year. </seg>
<seg id=10> 60% of the deaths are due to Newcastle Disease. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> He said that no order has been issued for the mass killing of poultry. </seg>
</p>
<p>
