<seg id=3> The Democratic Progressive Party wishes to work hand in hand with democratic parties of other countries by this means and share its development experience in democratic progress with other countries, make contribution to peace, stability and prosperity of Asia and realize the ideal of "Asian Democratic League" as early as possible. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Today when the international situation changes instantly fast, the fluctuation of regional powers causes changes in the entire world and the security of every nation is on trial. </seg>
<seg id=5> As far as the Asian and Pacific region is concerned, North Korea who is arrogant to have nuclear facilities has trial-launched missiles many times since US started its war against Iraq last month. The missiles flew over Japanese territorial sky. Besides, China has accelerated its arms expansion and aimed its missiles at Taiwan since long time ago. </seg>
<seg id=6> All of this has posed a great menace to the security of Taiwan, Japan and the whole Asian-Pacific region. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Such issues as related to consolidating democracy and maintaining security can only be discussed and solved through a formal security mechanism. </seg>
<seg id=8> Today's conference is the first formal dialogue on security between the Democratic Progressive Party in power in Taiwan and the Liberal Democratic Party in power in Japan and parliament members of other political parties. Its importance is obvious. </seg>
<seg id=9> I myself hope that, in addition to the bilateral dialogue between Taiwan and Japan, the peripheral countries of Asian-Pacific region like US, Japan and South Korea will work together to promote the establishment of "a security dialogue mechanism", to support Taiwan in participating in the multi-lateral dialogues and to implement the spirit of "cooperative security". </seg>
