<DOC docid="DPP20030902.001" sysid="che">
<p>
<seg id=1> Today it is an important moment which encourages us to continue our march on the road of reform. We give our highest regard to all the comrades in the party who embody our Party spirit and endeavor to achieve the goal of reform together. </seg>
<seg id=2> "Political parties withdrawing from the radio and TV media" is the most fundamental requirement of medium reform and also the idea which the Democratic Progressive Party has always adhered to. The Democratic Progressive Party in power will accelerate the pace of reform instead of being a hindrance or a burden. </seg>
<seg id=3> We are also aware that to achieve this goal the Party members of public service should take the lead to leave media. Although this is a small step in the reform, it is also a key step. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> In the past age of martial law and medium monopoly, many of the Party comrades, in order to strive for an open space for public opinion, have shouldered the difficult mission to set up the 4th TV station and local broadcasting stations. They wished to break through the existent limitation and add vigor to promote the reform of medium environment by this means. </seg>
<seg id=5> For example, Comrade Trong Chai took painstaking efforts for the birth of the 4th TV station and "Formosa Television" was born at last. </seg>
<seg id=6> This success had considerable impact on the whole medium environment. It broke up the monopoly by 3 stations and created larger space for the progress of CATV. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> But we must know that there are many deeds we have to do in the process of reform due to limits of historical environment. Therefore, today's complete open and free medium space represents the achievement of some periodic tasks. To continue the reform process, we have to give up things and make sacrifice. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The standing members of the Party Central Committee demand that all the party members of public service withdraw from TV medium business before the next session of the legislative opens. i.e. before September 5 so as to set an example and honor their promise to the people. </seg>
<seg id=9> We greatly appreciate all your efforts to adhere to Party's ideals and goals, including Trong Chai, Chang Chun-hsiung, Chou Ching-yu, Hou Shui-sheng, Kao Meng-ting, Hwang Nai-hui and Shen Ming-gong who gave up their personal interests to promote the medium reform. </seg>
