<DOC docid="FMPRC20031102.001" sysid="che">
<p>
<seg id=1> Asia is the largest continent in the world. Its area is nearly 30% of the earth's land surface and now its population accounts for about 60% of the whole world. Its total economic volume takes up one fourth of the world's total. It should and is well capable of making outstanding contributions to the world's peace and development. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=2> Asia has long and brilliant cultures. The drainage areas of the Yellow River and the Yangtze, the Indus and the Ganges valleys, and the reaches of the Euphrates and the Tigris are famous birthplaces of human civilizations. </seg>
<seg id=3> In the long process of historical development the Asian peoples have written splendid chapters for the development of human civilization. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> In modern times Asian has experienced hardships and sufferings. People of various country have made unremitting efforts for liberation and development and have gained tremendous achievements. </seg>
<seg id=5> But there is still a long way to go if Asia wishes to have a new rise and to enjoy new prosperity. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> To strengthen cooperation, promote development and achieve win-for-all is a way Asia must follow in order to rise and become prosperous. It is also where the fundamental interest of the Asian people lies. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> In the new situation of the new century Asian development faces new opportunities. </seg>
<seg id=8> Peace and development are the themes of the contemporary world and the overall peaceful international environment provides favorable external conditions for Asian development. </seg>
<seg id=9> The deepening economic globalization, the giant strides of the world technological revolution, the optimizing regrouping of international production factors and the accelerated industry transfer are favorable for Asian countries to utilize international capital, introduce advanced technologies, expand the world market and promote the economic development of their own countries. </seg>
<seg id=10> Asian, with rich resources and vast markets, is an area in the world with the greatest economic vitality and with tremendous potentials for development. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
<DOC docid="FMPRC20031210.001" sysid="che">
<p>
<seg id=1> Great population and under-development are the two state conditions of China. </seg>
<seg id=2> With 1,300 million people in China, any problem, no matter how insignificant it may be, will become a big one if multiplied by 1,300 million. Any financial or material power, no matter how tremendous it may seem to be, will become a very very low level if divided by 1,300 million. </seg>
<seg id=3> This is what the Chinese leaders must bear in mind at all times </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> To solve the problems of the 1,300 million people, we can depend on none other than ourselves. </seg>
<seg id=5> Since the People's Republic of China was founded, we have achieved a lot in our construction. But we have taken a roundabout course and lost some opportunities. </seg>
<seg id=6> Since we initiated reform and opening-up in 1978, we have finally found at last a right path for our own development. </seg>
<seg id=7> In other words, the Chinese people should build socialism with Chinese characteristics in an independent way. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The essence of this path is to mobilize all positive factors, liberate and development productive forces and respect and guarantee the freedom of the Chinese people to pursue happiness. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> The reform and opening-up in China spread from the rural areas to the cities, from the economic realm to the fields of politics, culture and society. </seg>
<seg id=10> In the final analysis, each step further aims at giving free play to all energy and initiatives of labor, knowledge, technology, management and capital and letting all sources of creating social wealth to flow completely. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
<DOC docid="FMPRC20031217.001" sysid="che">
<p>
<seg id=1> Profound changes have taken place in the world in recent years. Science and technology have developed by leaps and bound; the world production level has kept rising; links of the world market are increasingly closer. All this offers historic opportunities for the development of all countries. </seg>
<seg id=2> However, what is noteworthy is the fact that power politics, regional conflicts, terrorism, epidemic diseases, the worsening of environment, etc. pose great threat to the world stability and development. </seg>
<seg id=3> The negative influence of economic globalization add to the risks and costs for the economic and social development of developing countries. Some developing countries even face the danger of being out of mainstream. </seg>
<seg id=4> Presently the world economy still faces a lot of uncertain factors although it is steadily being recovered. </seg>
<seg id=5> The Doha round of multi-lateral trade talks suffered a setback. Trade protectionism and other complicated factors increase the difficulties for developing countries. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> What is gratifying is that the developing countries have taken a positive enterprising spirit, been bent on reform, hard-working stance and have made remarkable achievement. </seg>
<seg id=7> On the international arena developing countries, based on Non-aligned Movement and Group of 77, have strengthened their unity and cooperation and made important contributions for safeguarding their own legal interests and changing the irrational orders of the world politics and economy. They have become important forces for the promotion of democracy in international relations. </seg>
<seg id=8> In the meanwhile significant progress has been made in the exchange and cooperation between developing countries. The economic exchange between them has become more frequent. </seg>
<seg id=9> From the Andes to the Mekong, from the Union de Maghreb to the establishment of African Federation, the South-South Co-operation has kept enriching, improving and updating itself in both content and form, mechanism and means. </seg>
</p>
