<seg id=7> The leader of Taiwan authorities advocates the so-called "defensive public referendum" and "peaceful public referendum", which, in whatever package they may be, will only give rise to opposition and hostility across the Strait, further aggravate the tension and push the relations across the Strait gradually onto the edge of danger. </seg>
<seg id=8> This runs counter to the mainstream public opinion of Taiwan compatriots for peace, stability and development. It is misleading to and a control of Taiwan public instead of a deepening of Taiwan democracy. It is also a menace to the peace and stability of the Asian-Pacific region. It will undoubtedly meet with the general opposition of the compatriots across the strait and the international community. </seg>
