<DOC docid="HKN20040206.001" sysid="che">
<p>
<seg id=1> I extend my thanks to many parliament members who have voiced their opinions on administration of justice, laws, constitution, public servants and the support of organizational staff and public security in the "Government Policy Address" delivered by the chief executive. </seg>
<seg id=2> As for the category of judicial and legal service, only two parliament members Margaret NG and TSANG Yok-sing made speeches. They are chairman and vice-chairman of the Panel on Administration of Justice and Legal Services of the Legislative Council. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The Chief Executive puts forward many measures in his "Government Policy Address" to promote people-centered administration, including strengthening ties between chief officials and the society, conducting more researches in public policies, enhancing cooperation between the government and the Legislative Council, carrying out constitutional review seriously and carefully. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The Department of Justice will participate in all of the above work to ensure that all the government measures conform with laws and procedures, especially with the Basic Law, including the basic rights and freedom of citizens it guarantees. At the same time, it will keep alert, as a parliament member, Margaret NG mentioned, and safeguard the independence of legality and judicature in Hong Kong. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> As a chief official, I will do my best to solicit ideas and criticisms from the public and people in the legal circles on judicial affairs and issues of legal profession. </seg>
<seg id=6> For an example, CEPA results from close cooperation between the government and the legal circles such as Bar Association, Law Society, Association of China Appointed Attesting Officers. </seg>
<seg id=7> We have successfully included "Legal Service" into CEPA. It has become one of the open service trades on the mainland. It serves as a new platform for the cooperation in legal service and will bring about macro- and long-term benefits for both sides. </seg>
</p>
