<p>
<seg id=1> The last point is "Hong Kong people administering Hong Kong" which has become very familiar with all of us recently. The system requires that Hong Kong be administered by Hong Kong people whose main body consists of patriots. </seg>
<seg id=2> Patriots are judged by clear criteria. They must respect their own nation, sincerely support the state to resume its sovereignty over Hong Kong and never do anything harmful to the state and Hong Kong. Such people are patriots and constitute the main body of Hong Kong people that administer Hong Kong. </seg>
