<DOC docid="PD20031124.001" sysid="che">
<p>
<seg id=1> Bush failed to achieve his purpose in visiting Britain. There are many reasons for this. The most important reason is that US became the sole super-power after the cold war was over. It regards all the other countries as insignificant and its unilateralism keeps expanding. </seg>
<seg id=2> US, without being authorized by UN, launched the war against Iraq. It does not respect the opinions of its main allies on important international issues like the reconstruction of Iraq. It enrages most of the countries by doing things at its own will. </seg>
<seg id=3> A public opinion poll released by the Commission of the European Communities shows that 68% of the EU citizens do not think US had ample reason to launch the Iraq war and 53% believe that US has posed a threat to world peace. </seg>
