<p>
<seg id=1> Recently, subtle changes have taken place in the mainstream reports of Japan's media on the economic development in China. </seg>
<seg id=2> Contrary to the past "theory of China threat", many reports in Japan now hold that China's economic development is helpful to the recovery of Japan's economy and China's big growing market demand is an important impetus to Japan's economic development. </seg>
<seg id=3> The US "Newsweek" recently said in an article that the rise of China is an opportunity instead of a menace to other countries especially to its neighbors. </seg>
<seg id=4> The wide-spread "theory of China threat" is being replaced by "theory of China opportunity". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> "Theory of China threat" asserts that the development of China poses a threat to other countries, especially to its neighbors. </seg>
<seg id=6> However this provocative instigation of assumption has not been accepted by China's neighbors. </seg>
<seg id=7> The former Malaysian premier Mahathir once said straight away: "Asian countries need not be afraid of China's growing military and economic power, for China does not have the tradition of conquering other countries." </seg>
<seg id=8> The Indian Defense Ministry also believes in one of its long-term plans that China constitutes no threat to India. </seg>
<seg id=9> In trade governments and enterprises of different countries regard China as their best choice to expand their markets. Overseas investors of big picture firmly illustrate the "theory of China opportunity" with actions: over 400 of the world 500 top enterprises have invested in China. </seg>
<seg id=10> China has ranked among the top countries in the world in absorbing foreign investment for several years on end. </seg>
</p>
