<hl>
<seg id=1> A Traffic Accident in Zhejiang with Two Cars Crashed into Each Other, 3 People Killed </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency in Hangzhou on January 1st (Fang Lie and Zhang Hongming) An extraordinarily serious traffic accident took place in Ninghai County of Zhejiang Province early in the morning. </seg>
<seg id=3> An overloaded car and a large truck collided due to heavy fog. Of the 7 people in the car, 3 were killed and 4 injured. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> About 2 o'clock on the morning of first, a "Red Flag" taxi with the license plate number of "Zhe" BT 8705 driven by a Mr. Hua was on its way from Linhai to Ninghai with 6 passengers aboard. </seg>
<seg id=5> The road was fog-locked and the visibility was poor. </seg>
<seg id=6> At 60 km and 700 meters on Yong-Lin Line, the taxi collided with a truck with half trailer (license plate number: "Ji" B 35378) going in the same direction. </seg>
<seg id=7> It is said that the truck was running from the overtaking lane to the main lane. It was too late for the taxi to dodge which ran into the base of the truck from the middle of the truck and was seriously deformed. Of the 7 people in the taxi, 3 were killed on the spot including the driver. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> After the accident, the traffic police of Zhejiang Province promptly issued a circular demanding the traffic police departments of the whole province to take measures to intensify traffic control in harsh weather, to prevent overloading and speeding so as to ensure traffic security during the spring festival. </seg>
</p>
