<hl>
<seg id=1> Shenzhen Authorities Exercise SARS Quarantine on Drivers Who Enter or Leave China </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency in Shenzhen on January 8th (Reporters Li Nanling and Hong Wen) To prevent the spread of SARS and protect people's health, Shenzhen Inspection & Quarantine Bureau made an announcement recently that starting from 9th all drivers entering and leaving China shall have their temperature taken and complete health quarantine declarations at the 3 land ports of Huanggang, Wenjindu and Shatoujiao. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> It's said that it is difficult to ensure smooth traffic and exercise health quarantine of all drivers at the same time, because of heavy traffic at the Shenzhen ports, e.g. 25,000 vehicles pass Huanggang and 10,000 vehicles pass Wenjindu every day. </seg>
<seg id=4> In order to do a good job in taking temperatures and inspecting health quarantine declaration cards, Shenzhen Inspection & Quarantine Bureau conquered difficulties, in addition to transferring hands from its departments to reinforce the forefronts, these days has recruited over 250 people who have been dispatched to the ports after being trained so as to guarantee the land port safe and without traffic . Meanwhile, the Bureau has purchased 60 more infrared temperature-taking instruments to meet the needs. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Shenzhen Inspection & Quarantine Bureau has notified the relevant organizations and the entry & exit drivers that Health Quarantine Declaration Cards are available at the quarantine offices of the ports where Quarantine Supervision Book for Entry & Exit Vehicles and Goods (Personnel) is renewed, or at the working points of the ports where temperatures are taken and health quarantine declaration cards are inspected. </seg>
<seg id=6> The Bureau also calls upon related organizations and the entry & exit drivers to cooperate with its work to prevent SARS spreading into or out of China from Shenzhen ports with an aim to preserve people's health. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
<DOC docid="XIN20040108.0205" sysid="che">
<hl>
<seg id=1> (International) The Exchange Rate of USD Has Again Fallen into A New Low </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Xinhua News Agency in New York on January 8th) Influenced by the speech of the President of European Central Bank, the USD exchange rate has fallen to a new low on 8th after a brief rise on 7th. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> European Central Bank President Jean Claude Trichet delivered a commentary that day, saying that the over high Euro exchange rate would affect the export of European enterprises. But he believes that the gradual recovery of world economy and the growth of consuming demands partly offset the impact of the upward revaluation of Euro. </seg>
<seg id=4> In the meanwhile he points out that the strong Euro plays a positive role in stabilizing prices in Euro regions to some extent. Therefore, European Central Bank decides to maintain the original exchange rate. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Investors regard the commentary as a signal to show that officials in the Euro regions are not worried about the upward revaluation of Euro. As a result they keep selling USD, leading to an all-round low price parity of USD in relation to major western currencies with the British pound-USD exchange rate reaching a record high in 11 years. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The exchange rate between Euro and USD rose from 1:1.2640 on previous trading day to 1:1.2761 when the New York Foreign Exchange Market closed on 8th. The float of other exchange rates is as follows: the rate between British pound and USD rose from 1:1.8180 to 1:1.8320 (to 1:1.8354 at one point); that between USD and Japanese Yen fell from 1:106.27 to 1:106.17; that between USD and Swiss Francs fell from 1:1.2398 to 1:1.2267. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
