<seg id=4> -- To promote the establishment of a systematic cooperation between lawyers on the two sides so as to complement and benefit each other. </seg>
<seg id=5> The Department of Justice suggests that within the framework of CEPA legal service cooperation agreements be concluded with the provinces and cities on the mainland so as to promote a systematic collaboration. </seg>
<seg id=6> So far the Department of Justice has signed cooperation agreements with Beijing and Shanghai. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> -- To continue introducing and recommending Hong Kong as a center of legal service and dispute mediation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> -- To set up an information web site for legal service which provides data of lawyers from Hong Kong and mainland and will also hopefully include data of lawyers from Macao and Taiwan. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> After CEPA began to be implemented on the 1st of the month, Hong Kong lawyers may start to expand their mainland market through many ways, e.g. establishing joint management of law firms with mainland lawyers, being engaged by mainland law firms as advisors of Hong Kong law, or starting limited business on the mainland after acquiring the qualification of PRC lawyers. </seg>
