</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency in Beijing on January 15th (Reporter Du Yu) Ministry of Agriculture and State General Administration for Quality Control, Inspection and Quarantine jointly issued a notice, prohibiting import of artiodactyls and their products from Tajikistan. Those that have arrived at the ports of China shall be rejected or destroyed. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> According to a report of the World Animal Health Organization, 3 cases of foot-and-mouth disease type A viruses have erupted recently in Tajikistan. </seg>
<seg id=4> To protect the China's animal husbandry, the notice issued jointly by Ministry of Agriculture and State General Administration for Quality Control, Inspection and Quarantine also prohibits post artiodactyls and their products either mailed by post offices or brought by travelers from Tajikistan. </seg>
<seg id=5> Once found, all must be returned or destroyed. </seg>
<seg id=6> All birds, poultry and their products on international ships, aeroplanes, trains and other transport means that pass or stay in China shall be sealed up for disposal if found to come from South Korea. All their wastes and swill shall be disposed of under the supervision of the entry inspection and quarantine authorities. Nobody is allowed to dispose of them without supervision. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The notice demands that all the artiodactyls and products from Tajikistan confiscated by Customs or border defence as smuggled goods shall be destroyed under the supervision of the entry inspection and quarantine authorities. </seg>
</p>
