<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency in Paris on January 15th (Reporter Xu Zhenqiang) The European Airbus Company made an announcement on 15th that it delivered 305 planes in 2003, more than the predicted 300. For the first time it overtook the American Boeing Company and became the first in the world. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The delivery of Airbus Company last year was a little more than 2002 year's 303 planes. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Airbus Company predicts the market is still sluggish this year. So its delivery amount will be "approaching 300". </seg>
<seg id=5> The American Boeing Company announced earlier this month that its delivery of last year was 281 and its prediction for this year's delivery is between 275 and 290. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> In 2003 the proportion of Airbus Company delivery in that of the whole world rose to 52% and its proportion in 2001 and 2002 were respectively 38% and 44%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Last year the Airbus Company received 284 orders involving a total 32.8 billion USD. With 30 orders cancelled halfway, the actual order number was 254, accounting for 52% of the global total. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Senior executives of European Aeronautic Defence and Space Company which holds 80% of the Airbus Company shares said they don't expect the market of civil aeroplanes to recover very soon. They wish, however, that the Airbus Company could keep the present delivery level to 2005. </seg>
