<seg id=5> As for import, due to the increase of demand for petroleum and natural gas and the rocketing of prices, Japan's total import in 2003 increased by 5% over the previous year, also reaching a historical record of 44,320.2 billion Japanese Yen. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Japan's favorable balance of trade in 2003 was 10,238.7 billion Japanese Yen, a 3.6% growth over the previous year. It exceeded 10,000 billion Japanese Yen once more after 3 years. </seg>
