<hl>
<seg id=1> (International) The World Trade Organization (WTO) Submitted The Dispute over "Byrd Subsidy" to Arbitration </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency in Geneva on January 26th (Reporter Li Jie) The WTO announced on 26th that the complaint by EU and other 7 WTO members for sanction against American "Byrd Subsidy" has been submitted to the arbitration authorities. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> This complaint for sanction originates from the fact that US has failed to cancel "Byrd Amendment" before the deadline set by WTO. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Byrd Amendment passed by US Congress in 2000 demands the US government to use the punitive tax from anti-dumping and anti-subsidy cases to compensate those US companies whose interests are damaged instead of submitting it to the US Department of Finance. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> This practice of US was opposed by its major trade partners like EU, Japan, etc. </seg>
<seg id=6> The WTO made its final decision in January 2003 that this amendment violates the world trade rules and demanded the US to cancel it before December 27th. </seg>
<seg id=7> But US has not implemented the decision of the WTO. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> For this EU, Japan, Canada, Brazil, India, South Korea, Mexico and Chile applied to WTO recently to have the right to levy added tariffs similar in amount to American government subsidy on some of the products from US. </seg>
<seg id=9> But later US questions the extent of sanction and the legality of the complaint. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
