<DOC docid="ZBN20040310.002" sysid="che">
<p>
<seg id=1> First of all, whether the Taiwan situation is within or beyond the estimation of Beijing. </seg>
<seg id=2> Nobody but Beijing itself knows how it estimates the situation. But the result of the estimation can be inferred from some public phenomena. </seg>
<seg id=3> For 4 years Chen Shui-bian and Annette Lu of the independent camp have been clear-cut in rhetoric, smart and diligent in action and progressive and aggressive in independent endeavor. </seg>
<seg id=4> On the contrary Beijing, except for occasional high-pitched rhetoric, is close to routine in its attitude and seems indifferent to the progress of Taiwan independence. </seg>
<seg id=5> But since the fall last year, it has become entirely different, as if an ox-cart changes into a car. Since several months ago, It has been obvious that its handling capacity is completely different from that in 1990s. </seg>
<seg id=6> Judging from this, the Taiwan situation is within its estimation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Secondly, we must look at its diplomacy related to Taiwan. </seg>
<seg id=8> As for the development of Taiwan Strait situation, we must find out whether the attitude of important countries like the USA is near to that of Beijing, or to that of Taiwan. </seg>
<seg id=9> As the attitudes of countries are open, the answer is clear. </seg>
<seg id=10> Up till now those countries become closer to Beijing and have more contact with it while they get further away from Taiwan and had relatively little contact with it. And they begin to give "light words and earnest wishes" advice to Taiwan democracy which has been acclaimed. </seg>
</p>
