<seg id=2> There has been no better way to assess the performance of the Consumer Council than finding out if the rights and interests of consumers have been substantially improved. </seg>
<seg id=3> I strongly agree with what Chairman Chen just said.  After thirty years, not only consumers have become clearly aware of their own rights and interests, but also their rights and interests are valued by all sectors of society.  This is the result of hard work by both the Consumer Council and the government. </seg>
