<p>
<seg id=1> Japanese Prime Minister Junichiro Koizumi's "academic records" of "studying in London for two years" were exposed by the Japanese media as an exaggeration. </seg>
<seg id=2> The Japanese newspaper "The Weekly Post" verified with the Office of Registrar at London University and found that during his nine-month stay in Britain, Koizumi only audited a few classes as a part-time student at the university and did not earn any academic degree. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The Chinese domestic media, big and small, vied with one another in reporting or reprinting this scandal to the great gratification of the general public. </seg>
</p>
